video_title: You only have to be able to do half
transcript:
this is something that I figured out
from long distance running you only have
to be able to do half why because once
you get to the halfway point and you
have a half left you already have
empirical evidence that you can do the
remainder because it's exactly equal to
what you've already done
so this is really useful about breaking
down big projects or long distance runs
you only have to be able to do half and
that's enough proof that you can
complete the task
